    {
      "id": "graph-reference-minimap-smoke-guide",
      "type": "markdown",
      "label": "How To Test",
      "position": {
        "x": -460,
        "y": -240
      },
      "width": 1220,
      "height": 260,
      "visible": true,
      "showLabel": true,
      "data": {
        "markdown": "# Graph Reference Minimap Smoke Test\n\nThis graph is the dedicated smoke test for the `graph-reference` minimap preview model.\n\n## Target Behavior\n\nWhen a `graph-reference` is in `preview` mode, it should render **only the target graph minimap**.\n\n- the preview should identify the target as a graph artifact\n- task graphs and non-task graphs should both use the same minimap-style preview path\n- `graph-reference` should not switch between task-summary cards and iframe embeds in preview mode\n\n## Current Use\n\nUse this graph before and after the minimap implementation. Right now it will expose the old behavior. After the minimap renderer lands, all three references below should show distinct graph minimaps."
      }
    },
