    {
      "id": "graph-reference-minimap-smoke-note",
      "type": "markdown",
      "label": "Why This Matters",
      "position": {
        "x": 80,
        "y": 450
      },
      "width": 760,
      "height": 220,
      "visible": true,
      "showLabel": true,
      "data": {
        "markdown": "## Expected End State\n\n`graph-reference` should communicate **graph identity**, not imitate a node view.\n\nA minimap preview is the right surface because it:\n- keeps graph-reference semantically distinct from consume-view ports\n- works for both task and non-task graphs\n- avoids the current split between summary cards and embedded child runtimes\n- gives a stable visual cue before opening the referenced graph"
      }
    }
